
Overview of noun wildness

The noun wildness has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                       
1. (1) wildness, abandon -- (a feeling of extreme emotional intensity; "the wildness of his anger")
2. (1) ferocity, fierceness, furiousness, fury, vehemence, violence, wildness -- (the property of being wild or turbulent; "the storm's violence")
3. wildness -- (an unruly disposition to do as one pleases; "Liza had always had a tendency to wildness"; "the element of wildness in his behavior was a protest against repressive convention")
4. wildness -- (an intractably barbarous or uncultivated state of nature)
